.TH TWSU-TRAY 1 "July 2026" "tw-safe-update 1.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
twsu-tray \- TW Update Assistant system-tray service
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B twsu-tray
.SH DESCRIPTION
Background tray service (KDE StatusNotifierItem). By default the icon appears
only when a safe update is ready; left-click opens the status window,
right-click a quick menu. \(lqUpdate now\(rq and \(lqDetails\(rq run in a
Konsole terminal embedded in the window. Single-instance: launching it again
raises the window of the running service.
.PP
Normally started by the systemd user service
.BR tw-safe-update-tray.service ;
background checks are scheduled by
.BR tw-safe-update.timer .
.SH CONFIGURATION
.I ~/.config/tw-safe-update/tray.conf
.RS
.TP
.B show=safe\fR|\fBalways
When the tray icon is visible (default \fBsafe\fR).
.TP
.B notify=safe\fR|\fBreview\fR|\fBany
Which verdicts raise a desktop notification.
.TP
.B icon=\fINAME\fR
Freedesktop icon name for the tray (default \fBupdate-low\fR).
.TP
.B terminal=\fICMD\fR
Fallback terminal when the embedded Konsole part is unavailable.
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR twsu-check (1),
.BR twsu-update (1),
.BR twsu-details (1)
